fMC&pg=PA48#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Early Maps and Surveyors of the City of Washington, D.C.|year=1899|journal=Records of the Columbia Historical Society|publisher=[[Historical Society of Washington, D.C.|Columbia Historical Society]]|location=Washington, D.C.|volume=2|pages=48\u201371|issn=0897-9049|oclc=40326234|accessdate=2011-08-15|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/sketchoflifeofbe00tyso/page/n4/mode/1up|title=A sketch of the life of Benjamin Banneker: from notes taken in 1836: read by J. Saurin Norris, before the Maryland Historical Society, October 5th, 1854|first=Martha Ellicott|last=Tyson|location=Baltimore, Maryland|publisher=Printed for the Maryland Historical Society by John D. Toy|lccn=rc01003357|oclc=85794847|accessdate=2017-10-07|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uiug.30112037299119;view=1up;seq=5|title=Banneker's Almanack and Ephemeris for the Year of Our Lord 1793; being The First After Bisixtile or Leap Year and Banneker's almanac, for the year 1795: Being the Third After Leap Year: Afro-American History Series: Rhistoric Publication No. 202 (1969 Reprint Edition)|editor=Whiteman, Maxwell|publisher=Rhistoric Publications, a division of Microsurance Inc.|lccn=72077039|oclc=907004619|accessdate=2017-06-14|via=[[HathiTrust|HathiTrust Digital Library]]}}\n*{{cite book|first=George Washington|last=Williams|url=https://archive.org/details/historynegrorac05willgoog|work=History of the Negro Race in America from 1619 to 1880: Negroes as Slaves, as Soldiers, and as Citizens; Together with a Preliminary Consideration of the Unity of the Human Family, an Historical Sketch of Africa, and an Account of the Negro Governments of Sierra Leone and Liberia|title=Banneker The Astronomer|pages=[https://archive.org/details/historynegrorac05willgoog/page/n418 386]\u2013398|year=1882|location=New York|publisher=G. P. Putnam's Sons|lccn=09003580|oclc=6510556|accessdate=2017-10-07|via=[