{"title_page": "Abdelkader Ben Khemis", "text_new": "{{short description|Tunisian politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name         = Abdelkader Ben Khemis\n| image        =Abdelkader ben khemis.JPG\n| imagesize    =\n| smallimage   =\n| caption      =Abdelkader Ben Khemis in June 2013\n| order        =\n| office1      = Member of League of Human Rights - France\n| term_start1  = \n| predecessor1 =  \n| successor1   =\n| term_start2  = \n| term_end2    = \n| predecessor2 = \n| successor2   = \n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = 10 December 1942\n| birth_place  = [[Le Kef]] ([[Tunisia]])\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  = 15 August 2016\n| nationality  = [[Tunisian people|Tunisian]]\n| party        = [[Democratic Forum for Labour and Liberties]] (Ettakatol) \n| spouse       = \n| relations    =\n| children     = \n| Education    = \n| alma_mater   =\n| occupation   = Lawyer\n| profession   = Human right activist <br/> Politician\n| religion     = \n| website      =\n| footnotes    =\n}}\n'''Abdelkader Ben Khemis''' (Arabic: \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0627\u062f\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u062e\u0645\u064a\u0633), born on 10 December 1942 in [[El Kef]] and died on 15 August 2016, was a [[Tunisia]]n politician.\n\n== Biography ==\n=== A professor and an opposition figure ===\nHe graduated as a Doctor in organic chemistry in 1980, Abdelkader Ben Khemis was a master lecturer at National School of Engineering of Gabes of [[University of Gabes]]. This  was before taking a teaching profession in [[Monastir, Tunisia|Monastir]].<ref name=\"african\">{{cite web|title=D\u00e9c\u00e8s de l\u2019ancien d\u00e9put\u00e9 \u00e0 l\u2019ANC Abdelkader Ben Kh\u00e9mis|url=https://africanmanager.com/51_deces-de-lancien-depute-a-lanc-abdelkader-ben-khemis/|website=africanmanager.com|language=fr|date=16 August 2016|access-date=10 May 2018|publication-date=}}</ref> He was also a member of the Higher Education Union.\nAn opposition figure in [[Kef Governorate]] he was a founding member of [[Democratic Forum for Labour and Liberties]] (Ettakatol).He resigned from the party, to become independent.  He joined Al Joumhouri, then the Democratic Alliance, before being admitted to the Democratic and Social Way.\nOn 1 March 2001, (as reported by [[Lib\u00e9ration]]) \u201che was brutalized by the police while he was attending  a private ceremony organized by CNLT .<ref name=\"libe\">{{cite web|title=Agressions en Tunisie|url=http://www.liberation.fr/planete/2001/03/05/agressions-en-tunisie_356685|website=liberation.fr|language=fr|date=5 March 2001|access-date=10 May 2018|publication-date=}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 February 2006, he was \"arrested in front of his home in [[Monastir, Tunisia|Monastir]] by government agents and was interrogated for 3 hours at the headquarters of the National Security District, as reported by CNLT spokeswoman, [[Sihem Bensedrine]].<ref name=\"cnlt\">{{cite web|title=Conseil national pour les libert\u00e9s en Tunisie - Interpellation des membres dirigeants du CNLT|url=http://tunisnews.net/2016-05-22-12-23-05/item/4220-|author=Sihem Bensedrine|website=tunisnews.net|language=fr|date=10 February 2006|access-date=10 May 2018|publication-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Death ===\nAbdelkader Ben Khemis Died on 15 August 2016 as a result of an illness.  He is buried in Charfine Cemetery.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kef : d\u00e9c\u00e8s de l\u2019ancien d\u00e9put\u00e9 Abdelkader Ben Khemiss|url=http://kapitalis.com/tunisie/2016/08/16/kef-deces-de-lancien-depute-abdelkader-ben-khemiss/|website=kapitalis.com|date=16 August 2016|access-date=10 May 2018|publication-date=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{cat more|Democratic Forum for Labour and Liberties}}\n\n[[Category:National legislators|Tunisia Constituent Assembly]]\n[[Category:Constituent Assembly of Tunisia|Members]]\n[[Category:Members of constitutional conventions|Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Tunisian socialists]]\n[[Category:Tunisian social democrats]]\n[[Category:Tunisian secularists]]\n[[Category:Human rights in Tunisia|Activists]]\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Tunisian politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name         = Abdelkader Ben Khemis\n| image        =Abdelkader ben khemis.JPG\n| imagesize    =\n| smallimage   =\n| caption      =Abdelkader Ben Khemis in June 2013\n| order        =\n| office1      = Member of League of Human righs - France\n| term_start1  = \n| predecessor1 =  \n| successor1   =\n| term_start2  = \n| term_end2    = \n| predecessor2 = \n| successor2   = \n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = 10 December 1942\n| birth_place  = [[Le Kef]] ([[Tunisia]])\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  = 15 August 2016\n| nationality  = [[Tunisian people|Tunisian]]\n| party        = [[Democratic Forum for Labour and Liberties]] (Ettakatol) \n| spouse       = \n| relations    =\n| children     = \n| Education    = \n| alma_mater   =\n| occupation   = Lawyer\n| profession   = Human right activist <br/> Politician\n| religion     = \n| website      =\n| footnotes    =\n}}\n'''Abdelkader Ben Khemis''' (Arabic: \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0627\u062f\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u062e\u0645\u064a\u0633), born on 10 December 1942 in [[El Kef]] and died on 15 August 2016, was a [[Tunisia]]n politician.\n\n== Biography ==\n=== A professor and an opposition figure ===\nHe graduated as a Doctor in organic chemistry in 1980, Abdelkader Ben Khemis was a master lecturer at National School of Engineering of Gabes of [[University of Gabes]]. This  was before taking a teaching profession in [[Monastir, Tunisia|Monastir]].<ref name=\"african\">{{cite web|title=D\u00e9c\u00e8s de l\u2019ancien d\u00e9put\u00e9 \u00e0 l\u2019ANC Abdelkader Ben Kh\u00e9mis|url=https://africanmanager.com/51_deces-de-lancien-depute-a-lanc-abdelkader-ben-khemis/|website=africanmanager.com|language=fr|date=16 August 2016|access-date=10 May 2018|publication-date=}}</ref> He was also a member of the Higher Education Union.\nAn opposition figure in [[Kef Governorate]] he was a founding member of [[Democratic Forum for Labour and Liberties]] (Ettakatol).He resigned from the party, to become independent.  He joined Al Joumhouri, then the Democratic Alliance, before being admitted to the Democratic and Social Way.\nOn 1 March 2001, (as reported by [[Lib\u00e9ration]]) \u201che was brutalized by the police while he was attending  a private ceremony organized by CNLT .<ref name=\"libe\">{{cite web|title=Agressions en Tunisie|url=http://www.liberation.fr/planete/2001/03/05/agressions-en-tunisie_356685|website=liberation.fr|language=fr|date=5 March 2001|access-date=10 May 2018|publication-date=}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 February 2006, he was \"arrested in front of his home in [[Monastir, Tunisia|Monastir]] by government agents and was interrogated for 3 hours at the headquarters of the National Security District, as reported by CNLT spokeswoman, [[Sihem Bensedrine]].<ref name=\"cnlt\">{{cite web|title=Conseil national pour les libert\u00e9s en Tunisie - Interpellation des membres dirigeants du CNLT|url=http://tunisnews.net/2016-05-22-12-23-05/item/4220-|author=Sihem Bensedrine|website=tunisnews.net|language=fr|date=10 February 2006|access-date=10 May 2018|publication-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Death ===\nAbdelkader Ben Khemis Died on 15 August 2016 as a result of an illness.  He is buried in Charfine Cemetery.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kef : d\u00e9c\u00e8s de l\u2019ancien d\u00e9put\u00e9 Abdelkader Ben Khemiss|url=http://kapitalis.com/tunisie/2016/08/16/kef-deces-de-lancien-depute-abdelkader-ben-khemiss/|website=kapitalis.com|date=16 August 2016|access-date=10 May 2018|publication-date=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{cat more|Democratic Forum for Labour and Liberties}}\n\n[[Category:National legislators|Tunisia Constituent Assembly]]\n[[Category:Constituent Assembly of Tunisia|Members]]\n[[Category:Members of constitutional conventions|Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Tunisian socialists]]\n[[Category:Tunisian social democrats]]\n[[Category:Tunisian secularists]]\n[[Category:Human rights in Tunisia|Activists]]\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n", "name_user": "Will Sandberg", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdelkader_Ben_Khemis"}
